poler
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:one of a pair of bullocks in a bullock team [working on one side of the pole of a dray as 'nearside poler' on the left or 'offside poler' on the right.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
